<h2>Patient Visit Details</h2>
<hr />
<span class="title">Screen Overview </span><br />
<div class="clear"></div>
This screen is used to capture the patient’s visit details. At the registration counter patient gets the HIN Number, If HIN is not available then the patient details can be searched based on his name, service number or any other searching criteria available in the searching screen.
The HIN can also be capture through the Bar Coded OP label as an input.
Based on the search criteria the patient details will be displayed in a grid. And we can select the appropriate record.
<div class="clear"></div>

<br /><hr /><br />
<img src="images/adt_PatientVisitDetails.jpg" width="725"  /><br /><br />
<hr />
<span class="title"> Type :</span> 
<br />The Service type of the Patient. It will be a Display on the base of the record selected at visit search screen. It cannot have null values<br />
<span class="title">Service Number :</span> <br />
 It is a Service Number of the Service Personnel. It will be a Display on the base of the record selected at visit search screen. It cannot have null values.<br />
<span class="title">Service Status :</span> <br />
	The service status of the service personnel. It will be a Display field. It will be displayed on the basis of HIN. It cannot have null values.<br />
<span class="title">Relation :</span> <br />
	The Relation to the service personnel. It will be a Display field. It will be displayed on the basis of HIN. It cannot have null values.<br />
<span class="title">Name : </span> <br />
	The Name of the service person. It is a combination of Service Person First Name, Middle Name and Last Name. It will be a Display field. It will be displayed on the basis of HIN. It cannot have Null Values.<br />
<span class="title">Rank :</span> <br />
The Rank of the service Person. It will be a Display field. It will be displayed on the basis of HIN.
<p>
<span class="title">HIN No. :</span> <br />
	It will be a Display on the base of the record selected at visit search screen. It cannot have null values. It is a combination of Service Type, Service status, Service number, Relation to the service personnel and Serial No.<br />
<span class="title"> Name of the Patient :</span> <br />
	The name of the Patient. It is a combination of Patient’s First Name, Middle Name and Last Name. It will be a Display field. It will be displayed on the basis of HIN. It cannot have null Values.<br />
<span class="title">Sex :</span> <br />
	The Gender of the Patient. It will be a Display field. It will be displayed on the basis of HIN.<br />
<span class="title">Marital Status : </span> <br />
 	The Marital Status of the patient it will be a Display field. It will be displayed on the basis of HIN. It can have null values<br />
<span class="title">Age :</span> <br />
	The age of the patient. It will be a calculated field. The Age will be calculated on the Basis age entered at the time of registration and Current date. It will be a Display Field.<br />
<span class="title">Religion :</span> <br />
	The Religion of the patient. This value will come from Religion master. It will be a Display field. It will be displayed on the basis of HIN. It can have null values.<br />
<span class="title">District :</span> <br />
	The City/ District of the patient. It will be a Display field. It will be displayed on the basis of HIN. It can have null values. 
 </p>
  <p>
<span class="title">Visit No. :</span> <br />
	This is a system-generated number. It will get incremented every time of Patient visits the Hospital. At the time of registration if visit detail has been entered the visit no will be 1. It cannot have null Values.<br />
<span class="title">Visit Date :</span> <br />
The Date Of visit. By Default it will be Current system date. It cannot have Null Values.<br />
<span class="title">Visit Time :</span>	 <br />
The Time of visit. By Default it will be Current system time. It cannot have Null Values.  <br />
<span class="title">Department :</span> <br />
This will be a list element (Selectable) Here user can select the Consulting Department name. This value will come from department master table where the department type is "Consulting Room or OP Room". Default value will be "MI Room" It can have null Values.<br />
<span class="title">Token No. : </span> <br />
It is a System generated number. It should be Department and date wise. It is a display field.<br />
<span class="title">Consulting Doc. :</span> <br />
This will be a list element (Selectable) Based on the department selected, the doctor list will display. This value will come from employee master table where the employee type = "Doctor". It is a combination of Doctor’s First Name, Middle Name and Last Name. It cannot have null values.  
</p>
<p >
<span class="title">Complaint :</span> <br />
The Compliant of the Patient. This will be a list element (Selectable). The value will come from Compliant Master.<br />
<span class="title">Case Type :</span> <br />
This will be a list element (Selectable). This value has to come from a case type master table. It can have null values.<br />
<span class="title">Diagnosis :</span> <br />
	The Diagnosis given to the Patient. This will be a list element (Selectable). The value will come from Diagnosis Master. It can have null values.<br />
<span class="title">Disposed As :</span><br />
	Here user can enter Disposal type of the patient from hospital. This will be a list element (Selectable). The value will come from Disposal Master. </span>
	
<br /> <span class="title">Change By :</span><br />
The last change by will be updated automatically with the current login ID. It will update whenever the registration is updated. It cannot have null values.<br />
<span class="title">Change Date	:</span> <br />
The last change Date will be updated automatically with the current Date. It will update whenever the registration is updated. It cannot have null values.<br />
<span class="title">Change Time :</span><br />
The last change time will be updated automatically with the current time. It will update whenever the registration is updated. It cannot have null values.<br />
<span class="title">Save :</span><br />
 It allows to submit the forms. Validation will be checked if all are clear then it will submit the form. "S" should be the HOT Key.<br />
<span class="title">Reset :</span><br />
It will clear the Existing Record "R" should be the HOT Key<br />
<span class="title">Search : </span><br />
It will fetch records matching the given criteria and display the desired record. "E" should be the HOT Key 
</p>
